        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <aside class="quote no-group" data-username="linuxer" data-post="5" data-topic="530">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://forums.kicksecure.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/b5e925/48.png" class="avatar"> linuxer:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Do I need to increase size of virtual disk to run VMs in live mode?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>This isn’t a known issue, no.</p>
<p>But if you’re running on low disk space then it could coincidentally be triggered by running live mode.</p>
<p>This is about the host disk being full. Not the VM disk. The VM disk doesn’t result in a host error popup. You get faster help by just just pasting such error messages into search engines.</p>
